Setup

First import setup

  • This creates a settings.yaml file from a template in a new directory (~/.lemonade)
  • Then it loads global variables needed for everything like ..
    • DEVICE to GPU if it exists else CPU
    • Default paths for data (DATA_STORE), logs (LOG_STORE), models (MODEL_STORE) & experiments (EXP_STORE)
    • And some other variables used in pre-processing
  • Also import fastai.imports for all other required external libs
{% raw %} 
from lemonade.setup import *
from fastai.imports import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
DEVICE

device(type='cuda')
{% endraw %}

Setup dataset

{% raw %} 
DATA_STORE

'/home/vinod/.lemonade/datasets'
{% endraw %}

Next downoad Synthea 1,000 patients csv dataset into the raw_original folder in our datastore. The folder structre should look like below.

{% raw %} 
PATH_1K

'/home/vinod/.lemonade/datasets/synthea/1K'
{% endraw %}

For more details about the smalll dataset we are downloading, read the details on the Synthea website.

{% raw %} 
Path.mkdir(Path(PATH_1K), parents=True, exist_ok=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
synthea_url = 'https://storage.googleapis.com/synthea-public/synthea_sample_data_csv_apr2020.zip'
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
import requests
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
data = requests.get(synthea_url)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
with open(f'{PATH_1K}/data.zip', 'wb') as f:
    f.write(data.content)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from zipfile import ZipFile
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
with ZipFile(f'{PATH_1K}/data.zip', 'r') as zipObj:
    zipObj.extractall(PATH_1K)
{% endraw %}

Synthea zip creates a csv directory, the library requires it to be named raw_original, so just renaming ..

{% raw %} 
os.listdir(PATH_1K)

['csv', 'data.zip']
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
os.rename(f'{PATH_1K}/csv', f'{PATH_1K}/raw_original')
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
os.listdir(PATH_1K)

['data.zip', 'raw_original']
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
os.listdir(f'{PATH_1K}/raw_original')

['patients.csv',
 'observations.csv',
 'allergies.csv',
 'payers.csv',
 'careplans.csv',
 'medications.csv',
 'devices.csv',

 'supplies.csv',

 'providers.csv',
 'encounters.csv',
 'immunizations.csv']
{% endraw %}

Run pre-processing

Next run preprocessing

{% raw %} 
from lemonade.preprocessing.transform import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
preprocess_ehr_dataset(PATH_1K, today=pd.Timestamp.today(), from_raw_data=True)

The default settings for pre-processing generates patient data from 0 to 20 years of age, this can be changed by passing in a different age span (in years or months) to this function.

Run models

Create the data object

{% raw %} 
from lemonade.data import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
ehr_1K_data = EHRData(PATH_1K, LABELS)
{% endraw %}

Load vocabs and their dimensions

{% raw %} 
from lemonade.preprocessing.vocab import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
demograph_dims, rec_dims, demograph_dims_wd, rec_dims_wd = get_all_emb_dims(EhrVocabList.load(PATH_1K))
{% endraw %}

Get DataLoaders

{% raw %} 
train_dl, valid_dl, train_pos_wts, valid_pos_wts = ehr_1K_data.get_data()
{% endraw %}

Assemble everything needed for training

Loss functions

{% raw %} 
from lemonade.learn import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
train_loss_fn, valid_loss_fn = get_loss_fn(train_pos_wts), get_loss_fn(valid_pos_wts)
{% endraw %}

LSTM

{% raw %} 
from lemonade.models import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
model = EHR_LSTM(demograph_dims, rec_dims, demograph_dims_wd, rec_dims_wd).cuda() #.cuda() to be called before optim
{% endraw %}

Optimizer

{% raw %} 
optimizer = torch.optim.Adagrad(model.parameters())
{% endraw %}

Then run fit

{% raw %} 
h = RunHistory(LABELS)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from lemonade.metrics import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
%time h = fit(5, h, model, train_loss_fn, valid_loss_fn, optimizer, auroc_score, \
              train_dl, valid_dl, to_chkpt_path=MODEL_STORE, from_chkpt_path=None, verbosity=1)
